ivity. Those who learned the foundational calisthenics techniques might anticipate moving on to weight training rather than more complex calisthenics.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> H) However, in recent years, calisthenics has come back into vogue as a fitness trend. Excessive muscle development during bodybuilding is commonly associated with joint pain, injuries, imbalanced physiques, and poor cardiovascular health. Additionally, many people find that the heavy lifting and high volumes of reps used in traditional bodybuilding workouts make it difficult to engage the mind and maintain a positive attitude toward one\'s training. As a result, several of the most recent and well-liked gyms and programs emphasize calisthenics-based techniques. Numerous allied traditions, including yoga, Pilates, kettlebell training, gymnastics, and classical Greco-Roman calisthenics, are frequently incorporated into contemporary practices. Many individuals want to reclaim the ancient Greek understanding of physical excellence, physical sturdiness, and the harmony of the mind-body link.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>The text has eight paragraphs, A–H.</strong></p><p><br></p><p> <strong>For questions 21 – 30, choose options (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, or H). Which paragraph contains the following information?</strong></p>', 1146),
