(220, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Read the text below, then answer the questions. Six sentences have been removed from the text. Choose from the sentences (A – G) the one which fits each gap (12 – 17). There is one extra sentence which you do not need to use.</strong></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;<br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Title: The Marvels of Coral Reefs</strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Coral reefs are incredible ecosystems that provide a habitat for a diverse range of marine life. These underwater structures, formed over thousands of years by the accumulation of skeletons from coral polyps, are often referred to as the rainforests of the sea due to their rich biodiversity. <strong>(12) _____</strong> This relationship is crucial for the survival of many marine species, as the coral reefs offer protection, food, and breeding grounds.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>(13) _____</strong> Coral reefs face numerous threats, including rising sea temperatures, pollution, overfishing, and destructive fishing practices. Climate change, in particular, poses a severe risk as it leads to coral bleaching, a phenomenon where coral polyps expel the symbiotic algae living in their tissues, causing the coral to turn white and become more susceptible to disease.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Coral reefs are not only vital for marine life but also for human communities that rely on them for various reasons. <strong>(14) _____</strong> Additionally, coral reefs contribute to tourism and recreation, attracting visitors who want to explore the vibrant underwater ecosystems through activities like snorkeling and scuba diving.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>(15) _____</strong> Conservation efforts are underway globally to protect and restore coral reefs. Initiatives focus on reducing carbon emissions, establishing marine protected areas, and promoting sustainable fishing practices. Public awareness and education campaigns play a significant role in fostering a sense of responsibility and encouraging individuals to adopt eco-friendly practices.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>(16) _____</strong> Despite the challenges, the resilience of coral reefs provides hope for their survival. Scientists, conservationists, and communities are working together to develop innovative solutions and strategies to address the various threats facing these delicate ecosystems.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11px; line-height: 107%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>(17) _____</strong> As stewards of the planet, it is essential for us to recognize the value of coral reefs and actively participate in efforts to preserve these extraordinary ecosystems for future generations.</span></p>', 1315),
