(271, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Read the passage and answer all the questions below.</span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Climate Shifts on Earth</span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Our daily conversations often include discussions about weather changes, ranging from day-to-day fluctuations to more enduring shifts. Unlike daily or even monthly weather changes, climate change is a prolonged process, reflecting the average temperature and weather conditions in a specific location over years, potentially spanning hundreds, thousands, or even millions of years.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Diverse locations on Earth exhibit varying climates. For instance, deserts boast hot and dry climates, while rainforests generally experience warm and humid conditions. Certain mountainous regions and other locales maintain a consistent chill throughout the year.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">The term \"climate change\" frequently surfaces in contemporary discourse, primarily associated with the Earth undergoing a warming process, commonly known as global warming. While <span style=\"background: yellow;\">consensus</span> exists on daily weather patterns, debates may arise regarding climate change and global warming.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">The Earth, with its 4.5 billion-year history, has witnessed temperature <span style=\"background: yellow;\">fluctuations</span>, including Ice Ages, warming phases, and everything in between. Over the first 4.5 billion years, the Earth\'s climate experienced frequent shifts, according to scientific evidence. Nevertheless, it is irrefutable that the Earth\'s average temperature has escalated by 1.33°F in the past century, spanning from the 1900s to the 2000s. Although seemingly insignificant, this alteration holds potential long-term consequences for the planet.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Analogous to a greenhouse used by farmers and florists to nurture plants, the Earth is enveloped in a \'blanket\' that absorbs heat from the Sun. Greenhouses are notably warm. While the Earth isn\'t constructed of glass, the greenhouse effect describes the retention of the Sun\'s heat in the lower atmosphere through greenhouse gases.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Common greenhouse gases include carbon dioxide, methane, and nitrous oxide. These gases function like a protective layer, maintaining the Earth\'s average temperature at approximately 59°F, conducive for sustaining life. The <span style=\"background: yellow;\">amplification</span> of greenhouse gases intensifies the Earth\'s warmth, akin to a thicker blanket.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Certain climate change factors may be beyond human control, but several issues are undoubtedly influenced by human actions. Fossil fuels, located on or beneath the Earth\'s surface—comprising oil, coal, and natural gas—emit gases when burned, contributing to the formation of the Earth’s “blanket.”</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Farming practices also impact the greenhouse effect. When cows release methane gas t