hrough flatulence, over 1.5 billion cows globally contribute to the atmospheric \'blanket\' daily.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Trees and forests play a crucial role in absorbing carbon dioxide, one of the greenhouse gases. Through photosynthesis, trees emit oxygen, essential for all living beings. Unfortunately, the removal of trees and forests, termed deforestation, exacerbates the greenhouse effect, thickening the \'blanket.\'</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">A warmer temperature can adversely affect the world, leading to increased precipitation, irregular seasonal patterns, and heatwaves. The habitats of Arctic animals face jeopardy due to rising temperatures, posing threats to polar bears and seals. Orangutans in jungles are displaced by rising sea levels, and sea turtles lose breeding sites. Developing nations contend with challenges in farming due to heightened rain, floods, droughts, and potential limitations or increased costs of speci