(285, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 8px 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; font-size: 15px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Read the passage and answer all the questions below: </span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 8px 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; font-size: 15px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Instructions: Five sentences have been removed from the text. Choose from the sentences (A – G) the one which fits each gap (15 – 20). There is one extra sentence that you do not need to use.</span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 8px 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><br></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 18px;\">Born in the year of the dragon, China has always fascinated me. The Great Wall of China, a gigantic dragon spanning mountains and deserts, was something I had always wanted to see and walk on. And now, at last, this day had arrived.</span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">I arrived in Beijing, the Chinese capital,in July 2019.</span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">15. …?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"> I was gettingready as I stood at the entrance of Mutianyu, one of the Greater Beijingregion\'s best-preserved Great Wall portions. I had been putting off climbing it for so long.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">To get to the Great Wall of China, though,required me to climb what felt like a million stairs. Additionally, I had totravel a mountain cable car thereafter because the Great Wall of China is situated on mountains. Next, a number of more steps appeared. I was exhausted and thoroughly drenched in sweat when I at last arrived at the Great Wall of China. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">17…?</span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">It was fantastic to walk there. Ancientb troops could shoot arrows at the opponent through small holes in the brick walls, while the adversary was unable to properly shoot through them, allowing the soldiers to spy on their enemies and know when they were approaching without being spotted. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">19...? </span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">These fire towers sprouted dense smoke throughout the day or starting a fire at night to warn. As soon as the troops noticed any light or smoke, they lit eachfire tower individually to get ready for the invasion. That, in my opinion, is a rather secure and wise method of warning.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">I was worn out as I left the MutianyuGreat Wall. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">16. …?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"> I couldn\'t wait for my next journey to see more of the Great Wall. However, after returning to my hotel, I decided to learn more about this amazing wall.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 18px;\">I learned that the Great Wall of China wasconstructed in the past to strengthen China\'s northern frontier. Between the Chinese and different peoples throughout history, notably the Khitans during the Song dynasty, the Mongols during the Ming dynasty, and the Xiongnu during the Qin dynasty, the Great Wall has seen several fights and skirmishes.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black; background: yellow;\">20...?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"> Most of the construction was done along the ancient walls constructed by the Bei Qiand Bei Wei. The majority of the Great Wall as it is now was constructed under the Hongzhi emperor\'s rule (1487–1505). This section of the wall, which began west of Juyong Pass, was divided into south and north lines, known alternately as the Inner and Outer walls.</span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">Following the Ming, the Qing (Manchu)dynasty (1644–1911/12) implemented a new political strategy known as huairou (also known as \"mollification\") in an effort to appease the rulersand populations of Mongolia, Tibet, and other nations by refraining from interfering with their social, cultural, or religious affairs. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">18…?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"> And is now what it looks like today.</span></span></p>', 1380),
