ngregion\'s best-preserved Great Wall portions. I had been putting off climbing it for so long.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">To get to the Great Wall of China, though,required me to climb what felt like a million stairs. Additionally, I had totravel a mountain cable car thereafter because the Great Wall of China is situated on mountains. Next, a number of more steps appeared. I was exhausted and thoroughly drenched in sweat when I at last arrived at the Great Wall of China. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">17…?</span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">It was fantastic to walk there. Ancientb troops could shoot arrows at the opponent through small holes in the brick walls, while the adversary was unable to properly shoot through them, allowing the soldiers to spy on their enemies and know when they were approaching without being spotted. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">19...? </span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">These fire towers sprouted dense smoke throughout the day or starting a fire at night to warn. As soon as the troops noticed any light or smoke, they lit eachfire tower individually to get ready for the invasion. That, in my opinion, is a rather secure and wise method of warning.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">I was worn out as I left the MutianyuGreat Wall. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">16. …?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"> I couldn\'t wait for my next journey to see more of the Great Wall. However, after returning to my hotel, I decided to learn more about this amazing wall.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 18px;\">I learned that the Great Wall of China wasconstructed in the past to strengthen China\'s northern frontier. Between the Chinese and different peoples throughout history, notably the Khitans during the Song dynasty, the Mongols during the Ming dynasty, and the Xiongnu during the Qin dynasty, the Great Wall has seen several fights and skirmishes.</span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black; background: yellow;\">20...?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"> Most of the construction was done along the ancient walls constructed by the Bei Qiand Bei Wei. The majority of the Great Wall as it is now was constructed under the Hongzhi emperor\'s rule (1487–1505). This section of the wall, which began west of Juyong Pass, was divided into south and north lines, known alternately as the Inner and Outer walls.</span></span></span></p> <p style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; margin: 8px 0in 16px; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 19px;\">Following the Ming, the Qing (Manchu)dynasty (1644–1911/12) implemented a new political strategy known as huairou (also known as \"mollification\") in an effort to appease the rulersand populations of Mongolia, Tibet, and other nations by refraining from interfering with their social, cultural, or religious affairs. </span><span style=\"background: yellow;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">18…?</span></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"> And is now what it looks like today.</span></span></p>', 1385),
(291, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><em><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Read the Four extracts below on the theme of </span></em><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color: black;\">Virtual Reality</span><em><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">:</span></em></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Extract A</strong><br>Some people have a rudimentary grasp of technology but are not up to speed on the most recent goods on the market. On the other hand, other individuals are aware of the major headsets but are unfamiliar with some of the technology\'s terminologies and concepts. Virtual Reality or VR enables users to be completely immersed in a simulated world. <br>This is often given via head-mounted technology that monitors a person\'s motions. These VR headsets are made up of a screen (one for each eye, or two display panels) that comes in a frame (or headgear) that is fitted or strapped to your head.<br>There are three different types of volume in a VR. Setting a border or play area and being able to freely and physically roam about that area in the game is the essence of roomscale VR. The idea behind roomscale games is that you may physically walk about your space and interact with the simulated world and things inside it.<br>Standing and sitting are quite similar in that the user is supposed to stay essentially in the same spot and utilize various movement choices to mimic mobility rather than psychically moving across an area.<br><br><strong>Extract B</strong><br>Immersion is the sensation of being completely involved in a virtual environment. In contrast to monitor experiences, which we only see via a more-or-less distant window, things appear to be happening around us in VR. They appear near and immediate, even lifelike, especially when your entire body is participating in the connection. When you meet someone in Virtual Reality, you have the sensation that you are actually face-to-face talking to them.<br>The greater the immersion impact and the better the technology employed, the more imaginative the developed world will be. High-resolution screens with stereoscopic picture reproduction and fast frame rates attempt to make the depiction as accurate as feasible.<br><strong><br>Extract C</strong><br>Almost every mainstream VR headsets come with their own VR controllers that are tailored to the tracking technology. They imitate finger, arm, and hand movements and let users to engage with Virtual Reality by pressing a button or using analogue sticks or touchpads.<br>You may hold a controller in each hand at times to control various components of the experience. In certain circumstances, the controllers provide virtual depiction of your hands that allows you to orchestrate the environment and items inside it in ways similar to how you might in real life.<br><br><strong>Extract D</strong><br>However, in the future, VR control might go much further. VR attachments will allow you to control VR games with brain impulses. Many VR companies are researching brain-computer interfaces for gaming and VR. They believe that in the future, we will be able to influence our brains via external stimuli.<br>Mind control will be included into future VR and AR systems, according to many VR creators. The future of VR is set to bring input devices that use haptic feedback to attain a better level of immersion. Physical feedback will be sent to the user in the form of impulses or vibrations. You will be able to sense what\'s going on in the virtual environment, detect resistance, and even be able to feel the textures of items.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">For questions <strong>21 – 30</strong>, choose options (<strong>A, B, C, or D</strong>). Which do you think answers the questions? </span></span><br></p>', 1386),
