(312, NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Read the text below, then answer the questions. Six sentences have been removed from the text. Choose from the sentences (A – G) the one which fits each gap (12 – 17). There is one extra sentence that you do not need to use. </p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Artificial intelligence (AI) has the potential to revolutionize many sectors, and healthcare is no exception. Its implementation could change the way patients are diagnosed and treated. Despite the optimism, some researchers argue that the widespread use of AI in medicine is still a far-off goal. They point out that, despite several pilot projects, most healthcare providers still use traditional methods to deliver care. <strong>12 </strong>…………</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of the most promising areas of AI application in healthcare is diagnostics. Machine learning algorithms can analyze vast quantities of data quickly, potentially leading to early diagnosis and better treatment options. However, these technologies depend on having large datasets to train the algorithms, which can be a privacy concern for patients. <strong>13</strong> ………… Moreover, some argue that the cost of implementing AI solutions could be prohibitive for many hospitals, especially those in less developed areas. In contrast, proponents of AI argue that in the long run, these technologies could reduce costs by enabling more efficient care. <strong>14 </strong>………… While it is true that AI has not yet replaced human doctors, it is increasingly being used as a tool to assist healthcare professionals.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For instance, AI is being used to streamline administrative tasks such as scheduling and billing, freeing up more time for patient care. <strong>15 </strong>………… Despite these advances, however, AI is not without its critics. Some argue that AI systems lack the \'human touch\' that is integral to the provision of healthcare. They believe that empathy and interpersonal skills, which are vital components of patient care, cannot be replicated by a machine. <strong>16</strong> …………</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nevertheless, the general consensus is that AI has a lot to offer in the field of healthcare. The challenge will be to harness its potential while managing its limitations and potential risks. As research continues, it is likely that we will see AI playing an increasingly significant role in healthcare. <strong>17</strong> …………</p>', 1407),
