(318, NULL, '<p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Read the four extracts below on the theme of sea life. For questions 18 – 25, choose the option (A, B, C or D) which you think best answers the question.</strong></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></strong></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Extract A</strong> </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">There\'s something incredibly humbling about studying the intricate world beneath the sea surface. As a marine biologist, every time I dive, my worldly concerns seem to diminish in importance, replaced by the awe of the marine world around me. I\'ve been told to always respect the sea and its inhabitants, and that\'s something I\'ve taken to heart. A miscalculation in a dive or misunderstanding a creature\'s behavior can turn a peaceful study into a dangerous situation.Spending time by the sea always brings a certain degree of serenity to my life. I often find myself at the water\'s edge, my gaze following the movements of the seagulls as they swoop and dive over the sparkling water. The sea life here is rich and diverse, from the darting fish visible from the pier, to the crustaceans scuttling in the shallows. The sights, smells, and sounds of the sea create an atmosphere that allows my worries to float away on the tide.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Extract B </strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Marine life poses a wide variety of threats, one of which includes the notorious great white shark. Known for their formidable size and strength, these creatures rule the underwater kingdom, representing a potent danger for those unprepared or unaware. Nevertheless, the presence of these predators doesn\'t undermine the sea\'s potential for wonder and discovery, but rather highlights its complex and diverse ecosystem.Studying marine biology brings its own set of unique challenges and rewards. From understanding the complex interactions of various species within an ecosystem to unraveling the mysteries of deep-sea creatures, every day is a new adventure. The term \"holoplankton\" may not mean much to the average person, but to me, it represents a whole group of organisms that spend their entire lives in the water column, showcasing the astonishing adaptability of marine life.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Extract C </strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Embarking on my journey as a novice marine biologist, I faced a lot of skepticism and dismissive attitudes from my experienced peers. Understanding the science and the underwater world was not enough; I also had to learn the ropes of the unwritten rules, the insider language. I had to familiarize myself with terms such as \'pelagic\', \'benthic\', and \'zooplankton\' to engage effectively in discussions. Over time, I gained their respect and found my place in this unique community.The first time I set foot on a marine research vessel, I felt a profound sense of wonder mixed with anxiety. The vast expanse of water stretching out in all directions was a striking reminder of how much there was to explore and learn about marine life. The veterans of marine research barely noticed my anxious expression, caught up in their world of aquatic surveys and data collection. They talked animatedly, using jargon like \"pelagic\", \"demersal\", and \"benthic\", terms I would soon have to master.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Extract D</strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> Having been raised in an arid, desert town, my initial encounters with the vast, seemingly infinite ocean felt incredibly daunting. The sea, with all its unknowns and peculiar creatures, was a whole new universe. My unfamiliarity with the maritime environment and marine species felt overwhelming. Yet, I was determined to unravel its secrets. Slowly but surely, I learned to embrace the tides, the marine species, and the unpredictable weather, making the ocean my second home.There, beneath the water’s surface, the embodiment of power and grace moved with a lethal precision that sent a shiver down my spine. I remembered the warnings from my mentor, \"Respect the ocean and its creatures. The sea is home to life forms as beautiful as they are dangerous.\" That day, I truly understood what he meant. The ocean was a world of wonder and caution, teetering on the delicate balance of awe and respect.</span></p>', 1413),
