ht:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">became known as the \"photon theory” in later years.\" Etheric propagation was no longer necessary with the discovery of photons. The puzzling contradiction of why wave behavior was seen, however, remained unsolved. The Compton effect and the double-slit experiment\'s quantum variations were even stranger quantum variations, supporting the particle </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">interpretation</span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">After experiments were conducted and evidence gathered, the following conclusions were alarming:</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">“Light functions as both a wave and particle. Its nature depends on the circumstances of an experiment and the time of observations.”</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Now the next question was: Does such duality exist in matter as well? The de Broglie hypothesis, an expansion of Einstein\'s work to link the matter\'s wavelength to its </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">momentum</span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">, provided the solution. Successful investigations in 1927 verified the hypothesis, and de Broglie was awarded the Nobel Prize for his contributions.</span></p><br><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">It has been discovered that matter, like light, may display both wave and particle qualities depending on the circumstances. Massive objects have shorter wavelengths that are trivially tiny when thought of as waves. However, as demonstrated by the </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">double-slit</span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> experiment with electrons, wavelengths may be seen for smaller objects and are often greater.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Through a differential equation, wave-particle duality describes the physical behavior of light and matter. The </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Schrodinger </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">equation is used to represent a wave function in this equation. Simply said, the essence of quantum physics is the capacity to represent reality as waves.</span></p><br></strong></p><p></p>', 1425),
(331, NULL, '<p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b22b21e-7fff-bd3c-a794-46e3c92a3fba\"></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b22b21e-7fff-bd3c-a794-46e3c92a3fba\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Read the passage and answer all the questions below:&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: center;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b22b21e-7fff-bd3c-a794-46e3c92a3fba\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Wave-Particle Duality of Light</span></strong></p><p><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b22b21e-7fff-bd3c-a794-46e3c92a3fba\"><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Reality is what we make through the things we experience every day. However, </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">wave-particle</span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> duality is so absurd that it causes us to reconsider our fundamental assumptions. In accordance with the fundamental feature of matter known as wave-particle duality, the matter may operate both like a particle and like a wave simultaneously. According to this theory, depending on the situation, matter and light can display both wave-like and particle-like qualities. Although </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">complicated</span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">, the concept is one of the most </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffff00;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">fascinating </span><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:\'Times New Roman\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">concepts in physics.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"fon