(373, NULL, 'Jenson and Sam are brothers who attend the same university. The university is 18 km away from where they live. They both use skateboards to travel to the university. Jenson skates at a pace of 9 km/hr, while Sam can skate at a pace of 6 km/hr.', 1579),
(374, 'Austin: If I practice just as much as Tom, I will be able to master the skill just as quickly as him.', 'The more you practice a skill, the better you get at it. But it\'s also true that some people can master a skill faster than others with the same amount of practice.', 1580),
(375, 'Bobby: I just had an accident and I didn\'t have insurance. I’m definitely going to go bankrupt.', 'When people buy a new car, they typically take out insurance on it. This is to protect the car in case they have an accident. If people don\'t have insurance, then the financial loss will likely be very high in the event of an accident.', 1581),
(376, NULL, 'In a reading comprehension exercise, Sarah came across a passage describing Paris. The passage stated that Paris is a city in France. All cities in France have a significant history and architectural heritage. Paris, being a city in France, is depicted as having a significant architectural heritage.', 1582),
