(1144, 'the origin of the word ‘calisthenics.’', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'C', 'Indeed, the term calisthenics itself is derived from the Greek words for beauty and strength.', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1145, 'the last known supporter of calisthenics', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'E', '- Atlas was the last of a dying breed.', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1146, 'the first use of calisthenics as a training technique', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'B', 'a form of calisthenics by which they were building awe-inspiring physical strength and endurance', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1147, 'a multidisciplinary approach to all-round fitness and strength', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'H', '- many of the newest and most popular gyms and programmes emphasize calisthenics-based methods instead. Modern practices often combine elements from a number of related traditions such as yoga, Pilates, kettle-ball training, gymnastics and traditional Greco-Roman calisthenics.', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1148, 'wherefores the existence of calisthenics through the years', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'A', 'calisthenics uses only the body’s own weight for physical development', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1149, 'a medical substance to upsurge muscle mass and strength', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'F', 'These body builders also relied on free weights and machines, which allowed them to target and bloat the size of individual muscles rather than develop a naturally proportioned body', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
(1150, 'a reference to traveling showmen who exhibited their strength for viewers', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'D', '- This period is also when the phenomena of strongmen developed. These were people of astounding physical strength and development who forged nomadic careers by demonstrating outlandish feats of strength to stunned populations.', 83, NULL, 0, 1),
